itemLabel: William Clark, Baron Clark of Kempston

wikipedia_page.main: William Gibson Haig Clark, Baron Clark of Kempston,  (18 October 1917 – 6 October 2004) was a British Conservative politician who sat for a total of 29 years as a member of Parliament for three constituencies. He was also a Member of the House of Lords.
